Interface DataProperty<O,J>

  • Type Parameters:
    O - is the ontology.
    J - is the ground.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Axiom, Axiom.Descriptor<O,J>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    DataProperty.Disjoint<O,J,D>, DataProperty.Domain<O,J,Y>, DataProperty.Equivalent<O,J,D>, DataProperty.Range<O,J,Y>, DataProperty.Sub<O,J,D>, DataProperty.Super<O,J,D>, DataPropertyExpression, DataPropertyExpression.Disjoint<D>, DataPropertyExpression.Domain, DataPropertyExpression.Equivalent<D>, DataPropertyExpression.Range, DataPropertyExpression.Sub<D>, DataPropertyExpression.Super<D>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DataPropertyGround, DefinitionDataPropertyDesc, DomainRangeDataPropertyDesc, FullDataPropertyDesc, HierarchicalDataPropertyDesc

    public interface DataProperty<O,J>
extends Axiom.Descriptor<O,J>
    This interface is a part of the core of OWLOOP architecture. It contains interfaces of the expressions that can be applied to the OWL entity OWLDataProperty (i.e., OWLDataProperty).

    The expressions are the following:

    • DataProperty.Equivalent: this expression describes that a DataProperty is equivalent to another DataProperty.
    • DataProperty.Disjoint: this expression describes that a DataProperty is disjoint to another DataProperty.
    • DataProperty.Sub: this expression describes that a DataProperty is subsumes another DataProperty.
    • DataProperty.Super: this expression describes that a DataProperty is super-sumes another DataProperty.
    • DataProperty.Domain: this expression describes the domain restrictions of a DataProperty.
    • DataProperty.Range: this expression describes the range restrictions of a DataProperty.
